    <note>Huang(2) Lu [8066] Posthumously purged as Yuanfu coalition member. His ancestors were from Guangzhou, Gushi xian. They were an illustrious lineage (zhuzu) of Shaowu. Lu rose from commoner status (buyi) by obtaining the jinshi degree. In this instance, buyi seems to mean no more than that his immediate ancestors did not hold public office. Bosi's [7030] grandfather, Liu(2) Zhengfu's [8088] and Zhang(1) Gen's [255] father-in-law, and Zhang(1) Dao(2)'s [8019] maternal grandfather. Li(2) Gang's [8078] grandmother was his younger sister. Lu's father and Huang(2) Zhong's [843] great grandfather have the same generational name. SHY:ZG, 67.10b-11a; Fujian TZ, 147.19a (shige in 1056 treated as 1057 jinshi); Li Gang, WJ, 170.9b-10b. CBD, 4, 2871-2.</note>
